# --- Database (Supabase in production, local Postgres in dev) -----------
#
# In PRODUCTION (Supabase):
#   - DATABASE_URL points to the *Transaction Pooler* (port 6543) with pgbouncer=true.
#     Used by your app's runtime queries; safe under pgBouncer transaction mode.
#   - DIRECT_URL points to the *Direct Connection* (port 5432). Used by Prisma
#     for `migrate deploy`, `migrate dev`, and introspection. Required.
#
# In LOCAL DEV (docker-compose):
#   - Both can point at the same local postgres URL.
#
# Get these strings from: Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> Database -> Connection string
DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1
DIRECT_URL=